text: Norrie May-Welby (born 23 May 1961) is a Scottish-Australian transsexual person. Welby was the first person to be considered 'genderless'. ==Early life== May-Welby was born in Paisley, Renfrewshire. When Norrie was seven years old, the family emigrated to Western Australia. Welby has lived in Sydney since the early 1990s.http://www.abc.net.au/tv/enoughrope/transcripts/s927538.htm ==References== Category:1961 births Category:Australian activists Category:Australian LGBT people Category:Living people Category:Transgender people
